In October, Tymoshenko was sentenced to seven years in prison for allegedly entering into a disadvantageous contract with Russia over the purchase of natural gas.
The judgment is not yet in force and the appeal of the convicts is due to be heard in court in December.
Timoshenko himself calls the ruling a political revenge on the regime and even in the West the trial raised suspicions of the court's bias.
The motion to remove Paragraph 365 from the Criminal Code, which condemned the former Prime Minister, was supported by 147 Members.
226 votes would have been required to approve it.
